# KBOS Frontend

## Principles

- UI reflects filesystem hierarchy; folder `index.md` is the folder home.
- Fetch note content from API; never treat Bleve/graph/vector stores as source of truth.
- Work offline-first: cache reads; queue writes; surface sync/index status from server.
- Mermaid renders client-side. Encrypted notes: show locked state until unlock session (server-held key material only in memory).

## Structure (target)

```
app/              # Next.js routes
components/ui/    # shadcn
components/editor/  # markdown editor, wiki-link autocomplete
components/graph/   # knowledge graph, mind map views
lib/api/          # REST + WebSocket client
lib/types/        # DocMeta, SearchHit, VaultConfig
```

## UX surfaces (priority)

1. Vault tree + editor + backlinks panel
2. Search (fuzzy + `tag:`, `folder:`, `title:`, `status:`)
3. Tag explorer, task dashboard, templates picker
4. Graph / mind map / relationship views
5. AI panel with **cited** answers; scope: doc / folder / vault

## Theming

Support light, dark, auto, Nord, Dracula, Solarized via CSS variables — match shadcn theme tokens.

## API usage

- Prefer WebSocket for live index/update notifications.
- Optimistic UI for saves; reconcile on server ack or conflict.
